For this task, I used Canva to design an infographic on digital literacy.
My main aim was to make it simple and easy to understand so that any student can quickly go through it and get the basic idea. 
I included topics like the meaning of digital literacy, safe internet practices, and maintaining a professional online presence.
While creating the design, I focused more on clarity rather than adding too many design elements.
I used short points, simple icons, and a clean layout so that the information doesn’t look confusing or crowded. 
I tried different layouts before finalizing one that looked balanced.
One difficulty I faced was deciding what content to include because there is a lot of information related to digital literacy.
Since it was only one page, I had to remove some points and keep only the most important ones. This took some time and required careful thinking.
At the same time, I found this task quite interesting because it showed me how visual content can make learning easier.
Overall, this task helped me improve my ability to present information in a clear and effective way.
